# lifeline — Cursor adapter

**Harness:** cursor · **Tier:** FULL (Cursor ≥ 2.4; documented fallbacks otherwise)
**Plugin root:** `${CURSOR_PLUGIN_ROOT}` — resolve every `core/*`, `adapters/*`, and
`docs/*` path from there, not from the project repo root.

## Invoke the orchestrator

```
/lifeline-lifecycle start
/lifeline-lifecycle continue
/lifeline-lifecycle status
/lifeline-lifecycle abort
/lifeline-lifecycle debug <description>
/lifeline-lifecycle guide
```

Flags: `--auto` · `--retry-cap=N`. No slash commands in this session? Say:
`run the lifeline lifecycle <args>`.

## Primitive bindings (native → fallback)

| Primitive | Cursor |
|---|---|
| `@dispatch_agent` | Subagents (`adapters/cursor/agents/lifeline-*`), **parallel** per wave → inline sequential |
| `@ask_user` | Interactive Q&A tool → numbered text prompt (`adapters/cursor/prompt-conventions.md`) |
| `@persist_state` | `.lifeline/<scope>/state.json` + sessionStart hook surfacing |
| `@run_hook` | `hooks/hooks.json` (pre-commit deny gate, session-start resume, diff-size log) → soft self-checks, log `enforcement.advisory harness=cursor` |
| `@command_namespace` | `/lifeline-lifecycle` → invoke by name |
| `@artifact_root` | `.lifeline/<scope>/` in this repo |

